description:
&lt;p&gt;The Family &amp; Integrated Support Services Division, are seeking a confident individual to join our busy Secretarial Team within the Gynaecology Department as a Secretary to the Urogynaecology Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post reports to a Senior Medical Secretary. The post is for a Band 3 Part time (30 hours per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate a flexible, motivated approach to their work as well as preferably having previous experience as a Medical Secretary/secretarial assistant within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Validation of 18 week pathways is a key element of this role, therefore sound knowledge of 18 weeks RTT is essential for this post. Audio typing and word processing (RSA II or equivalent) would be an advantage and therefore desirable for all applicants. Being confident on the Telephone and taking messages and working knowledge of Microsoft Office is also required and good communication skills. Duties for the role include direct support to Medical Staff, dealing with enquiries from internal and external agencies, and liaising with other departments within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is rewarding and challenging, within a service division, which is continually changing and reassessing its administration systems in line with an ever-modernising NHS service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Emily O&#39;Neill on 01480 416440&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emily O&#39;Neill: Unit Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;emily.o&#39;neill6@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
